excerpt: Stone statues, wood carvings & other art displayed & sold at a Japanese-style Buddhist temple.
detail_description: Sudarshan Crafts Museum is a must-visit spot in Puri, offering a wide array of stone statues, wood carvings, and other exquisite art pieces. excerpt: This Kalinga-style sandstone Hindu temple dedicated to Jagannath is surrounded by gardens.
detail_description: Shree Gundicha Temple, located just 3 kilometers away from the main Jagannath temple complex in Puri, is a Kalinga-style sandstone Hindu temple surrounded by gardens. It serves as the summer retreat for Lord Jagannath and his siblings and marks the end of the Ratha Yatra festival, during which the deities rest there for seven days before returning home. The temple is usually empty except during this festival.

Every year, countless devotees from around the world flock to Puri to offer their prayers at this sacred place. According to mythology, Hanuman was appointed by Lord Jagannath to protect the temple and the city of Puri from sea damage.

excerpt: Puri, also known as Jagannath Puri, is a coastal city and a municipality in the state of Odisha in eastern India. It is the district headquarters of Puri district and is situated on the Bay of Bengal, 60 kilometres south of the state capital of Bhubaneswar. Wikipedia.
